<subSubSection id="C35A6551FFF69344FF6FFB26FE44FEC4" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="856" pageId="0" pageNumber="853" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BFF36DAFFF69347FF6FFB26FCD2FAD8" blockId="0.[178,1086,1258,1364]" pageId="0" pageNumber="853">
D e s c r i p t i o n: Forebody as in 
<figureCitation id="137B2A5FFFF69347FD9BFB27FD20FA8C" box="[582,651,1258,1280]" captionStart="Figs 1-7" captionStartId="1.[178,218,1237,1257]" captionTargetBox="[203,1071,308,1219]" captionTargetId="figure-51@1.[178,1093,753,1222]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs 1-7: Medon reuteri nov.sp.: (1) forebody; (2) head and pronotum; (3) elytra; (4) male sternite VII; (5) male sternite VIII; (6) aedeagus in lateral view; (7) aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 1: 1.0 mm; 2-3: 0.5 mm; 4-7: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5416628" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5416628/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="853">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
. Relatively small species, total length: 
<quantity id="4CB89B3FFFF69347FF6FFACBFEA9FA90" box="[178,258,1286,1308]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.7" pageId="0" pageNumber="853" unit="mm" value="3.7">3.7 mm</quantity>
; length from anterior margin of clypeus to posterior apex of suture: 
<quantity id="4CB89B3FFFF69347FC07FACBFB91FA90" box="[986,1082,1286,1308]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.95" pageId="0" pageNumber="853" unit="mm" value="1.95">1.95 mm</quantity>
. Coloration: Head blackish; pronotum and elytra light reddish brown; abdomen dark brown, with the apex reddish brown; legs and antenna reddish yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFF36DAFFF69347FF6FFAAFFE37F9B0" blockId="0.[178,1086,1378,1596]" pageId="0" pageNumber="853">
Head 0.96 times as long as wide (length measured from anterior margin of clypeus to posterior margin), of subquadrate shape; eyes moderately large (
<figureCitation id="137B2A5FFFF69347FC95FAB3FC2EFA18" box="[840,901,1406,1428]" captionStart="Figs 1-7" captionStartId="1.[178,218,1237,1257]" captionTargetBox="[203,1071,308,1219]" captionTargetId="figure-51@1.[178,1093,753,1222]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs 1-7: Medon reuteri nov.sp.: (1) forebody; (2) head and pronotum; (3) elytra; (4) male sternite VII; (5) male sternite VIII; (6) aedeagus in lateral view; (7) aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 1: 1.0 mm; 2-3: 0.5 mm; 4-7: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5416628" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5416628/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="853">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
) and weakly projecting from lateral outline of head, about half the length of postocular region in dorsal view; microsculpture distinct, therefore integument matt; puncturation in lateral area coarse and dense with interstices distinctly shallower than diameter of punctures, in anterior and central dorsal area less dense with interstices partly wider than diameter of punctures (
<figureCitation id="137B2A5FFFF69347FEF8F9C7FECCF9AC" box="[293,359,1546,1568]" captionStart="Figs 1-7" captionStartId="1.[178,218,1237,1257]" captionTargetBox="[203,1071,308,1219]" captionTargetId="figure-51@1.[178,1093,753,1222]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs 1-7: Medon reuteri nov.sp.: (1) forebody; (2) head and pronotum; (3) elytra; (4) male sternite VII; (5) male sternite VIII; (6) aedeagus in lateral view; (7) aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 1: 1.0 mm; 2-3: 0.5 mm; 4-7: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5416628" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5416628/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="853">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). Antennomeres of similar morphology as in other species of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C404D59FFF69347FBFCF9C6FEA9F9B7" baseAuthorityName="Kraatz" baseAuthorityYear="1857" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Medon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="853" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apicalis">
<emphasis id="B934EAC8FFF69347FBFCF9C6FEA9F9B7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="853">M. apicalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group (
<figureCitation id="137B2A5FFFF69347FE8CF9EBFE27F9B0" box="[337,396,1574,1596]" captionStart="Figs 1-7" captionStartId="1.[178,218,1237,1257]" captionTargetBox="[203,1071,308,1219]" captionTargetId="figure-51@1.[178,1093,753,1222]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs 1-7: Medon reuteri nov.sp.: (1) forebody; (2) head and pronotum; (3) elytra; (4) male sternite VII; (5) male sternite VIII; (6) aedeagus in lateral view; (7) aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 1: 1.0 mm; 2-3: 0.5 mm; 4-7: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5416628" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5416628/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="853">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFF36DAFFF79346FF6FFF16FCDAFEA7" blockId="1.[178,1085,219,299]" pageId="1" pageNumber="854">
Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="137B2A5FFFF79346FEF9FF16FEC9FF7D" box="[292,354,219,241]" captionStart="Figs 1-7" captionStartId="1.[178,218,1237,1257]" captionTargetBox="[203,1071,308,1219]" captionTargetId="figure-51@1.[178,1093,753,1222]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs 1-7: Medon reuteri nov.sp.: (1) forebody; (2) head and pronotum; (3) elytra; (4) male sternite VII; (5) male sternite VIII; (6) aedeagus in lateral view; (7) aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 1: 1.0 mm; 2-3: 0.5 mm; 4-7: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5416628" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5416628/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="854">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
) 1.05 times as wide as long and 0.96 times as wide as head; puncturation distinctly less coarse and dense than that of head, therefore with more shine; midline with narrow impunctate area; interstices with distinct microsculpture.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF3F6652FFF79346FF6FFB18FE5EFA92" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5416628" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5416628" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5416628/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="854" startId="1.[178,218,1237,1257]" targetBox="[203,1071,308,1219]" targetPageId="1">
<paragraph id="8BFF36DAFFF79346FF6FFB18FE5EFA92" blockId="1.[178,1085,1235,1310]" pageId="1" pageNumber="854">
<emphasis id="B934EAC8FFF79346FF6FFB18FF54FB65" bold="true" box="[178,255,1237,1257]" pageId="1" pageNumber="854">Figs 1-7</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName id="4C404D59FFF79346FED1FB1EFE24FB65" authority="Feldmann, 2007" authorityName="Feldmann" authorityYear="2007" box="[268,399,1235,1257]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Medon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="854" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reuteri" status="nov.sp.">
<emphasis id="B934EAC8FFF79346FED1FB1EFE24FB65" box="[268,399,1235,1257]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="854">Medon reuteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20757B3FFF79346FE4BFB18FE77FB65" box="[406,476,1237,1257]" pageId="1" pageNumber="854" rank="species">nov.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
: (
<emphasis id="B934EAC8FFF79346FE31FB18FE5CFB65" bold="true" box="[492,503,1237,1257]" pageId="1" pageNumber="854">1</emphasis>
) forebody; (
<emphasis id="B934EAC8FFF79346FDB1FB18FDDCFB65" bold="true" box="[620,631,1237,1257]" pageId="1" pageNumber="854">2</emphasis>
) head and pronotum; (
<emphasis id="B934EAC8FFF79346FC91FB18FCFCFB65" bold="true" box="[844,855,1237,1257]" pageId="1" pageNumber="854">3</emphasis>
) elytra; (
<emphasis id="B934EAC8FFF79346FC70FB18FC13FB65" bold="true" box="[941,952,1237,1257]" pageId="1" pageNumber="854">4</emphasis>
) male sternite VII; (
<emphasis id="B934EAC8FFF79346FF38FB3DFF5BFA88" bold="true" box="[229,240,1264,1284]" pageId="1" pageNumber="854">5</emphasis>
) male sternite VIII; (
<emphasis id="B934EAC8FFF79346FE6EFB3DFE15FA88" bold="true" box="[435,446,1264,1284]" pageId="1" pageNumber="854">6</emphasis>
) aedeagus in lateral view; (
<emphasis id="B934EAC8FFF79346FD66FB3DFD6DFA88" bold="true" box="[699,710,1264,1284]" pageId="1" pageNumber="854">7</emphasis>
) aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 1: 1.0 mm; 2-3: 0.5 mm; 4-7: 0.2 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BFF36DAFFF79346FF6FFAFBFE06FA2F" blockId="1.[178,1085,1334,1444]" pageId="1" pageNumber="854">
Elytra 1.17 times as wide and at suture 1.14 times as long as pronotum (
<figureCitation id="137B2A5FFFF79346FC42FAFBFC77FAC0" box="[927,988,1334,1356]" captionStart="Figs 1-7" captionStartId="1.[178,218,1237,1257]" captionTargetBox="[203,1071,308,1219]" captionTargetId="figure-51@1.[178,1093,753,1222]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs 1-7: Medon reuteri nov.sp.: (1) forebody; (2) head and pronotum; (3) elytra; (4) male sternite VII; (5) male sternite VIII; (6) aedeagus in lateral view; (7) aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 1: 1.0 mm; 2-3: 0.5 mm; 4-7: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5416628" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5416628/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="854">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
); surface relatively shiny; puncturation well defined, somewhat granulose (
<figureCitation id="137B2A5FFFF79346FC8CFA9EFC3BFAE5" box="[849,912,1363,1385]" captionStart="Figs 1-7" captionStartId="1.[178,218,1237,1257]" captionTargetBox="[203,1071,308,1219]" captionTargetId="figure-51@1.[178,1093,753,1222]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs 1-7: Medon reuteri nov.sp.: (1) forebody; (2) head and pronotum; (3) elytra; (4) male sternite VII; (5) male sternite VIII; (6) aedeagus in lateral view; (7) aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 1: 1.0 mm; 2-3: 0.5 mm; 4-7: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5416628" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5416628/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="854">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
); microsculpture not visible. Hind wings fully developed. Legs of similar morphology as in other species of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C404D59FFF79346FF2FFA43FECFFA2F" baseAuthorityName="Kraatz" baseAuthorityYear="1857" box="[242,356,1422,1443]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Medon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="854" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apicalis">
<emphasis id="B934EAC8FFF79346FF2FFA43FECFFA2F" box="[242,356,1422,1443]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="854">M. apicalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFF36DAFFF79346FF6CFA7EFDF7FA6A" blockId="1.[177,1084,1459,1510]" pageId="1" pageNumber="854">Abdomen with fine and relatively dense puncturation and microsculpture. Posterior margin of tergite VII with palisade fringe.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFF36DAFFF79346FF1AFA3BFB85F9CA" blockId="1.[177,1085,1525,1606]" pageId="1" pageNumber="854">
: posterior margin of sternite VII indistinctly bisinuate, without palisade setae, but with a row of long black stout setae (
<figureCitation id="137B2A5FFFF79346FDDBF9DEFDECF9A5" box="[518,583,1555,1577]" captionStart="Figs 1-7" captionStartId="1.[178,218,1237,1257]" captionTargetBox="[203,1071,308,1219]" captionTargetId="figure-51@1.[178,1093,753,1222]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs 1-7: Medon reuteri nov.sp.: (1) forebody; (2) head and pronotum; (3) elytra; (4) male sternite VII; (5) male sternite VIII; (6) aedeagus in lateral view; (7) aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 1: 1.0 mm; 2-3: 0.5 mm; 4-7: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5416628" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5416628/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="854">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
); posterior impression of sternite VIII relatively deep, U-shaped (
<figureCitation id="137B2A5FFFF79346FE88F9FDFE3BF9CA" box="[341,400,1584,1606]" captionStart="Figs 1-7" captionStartId="1.[178,218,1237,1257]" captionTargetBox="[203,1071,308,1219]" captionTargetId="figure-51@1.[178,1093,753,1222]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs 1-7: Medon reuteri nov.sp.: (1) forebody; (2) head and pronotum; (3) elytra; (4) male sternite VII; (5) male sternite VIII; (6) aedeagus in lateral view; (7) aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 1: 1.0 mm; 2-3: 0.5 mm; 4-7: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5416628" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5416628/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="854">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
); aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="137B2A5FFFF79346FDD4F9FDFDF0F9CA" box="[521,603,1584,1606]" captionStart="Figs 1-7" captionStartId="1.[178,218,1237,1257]" captionTargetBox="[203,1071,308,1219]" captionTargetId="figure-51@1.[178,1093,753,1222]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs 1-7: Medon reuteri nov.sp.: (1) forebody; (2) head and pronotum; (3) elytra; (4) male sternite VII; (5) male sternite VIII; (6) aedeagus in lateral view; (7) aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 1: 1.0 mm; 2-3: 0.5 mm; 4-7: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5416628" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5416628/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="854">Figs 6-7</figureCitation>
) of distinctive shape, especially in ventral view.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFF36DAFFF49345FF6FFF17FDECFEA4" blockId="2.[178,1085,218,296]" pageId="2" pageNumber="855">
C o m p a r a t i v e n o t e s: Based on the morphology of the aedeagus, as well as on the shape and chaetotaxy of the male sternite VII, the new species is a member of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C404D59FFF49345FF6FFEDFFE88FEAB" baseAuthorityName="Kraatz" baseAuthorityYear="1857" box="[178,291,274,295]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Medon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="855" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apicalis">
<emphasis id="B934EAC8FFF49345FF6FFEDFFE88FEAB" box="[178,291,274,295]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="855">M. apicalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group (sensu ASSING 2007).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFF36DAFFF49345FF6FFEFBFEECFDC4" blockId="2.[178,1085,310,584]" pageId="2" pageNumber="855">
The geographically closest representatives of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C404D59FFF49345FD1DFEFBFC9DFEC7" baseAuthorityName="Kraatz" baseAuthorityYear="1857" box="[704,822,310,331]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Medon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="855" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apicalis">
<emphasis id="B934EAC8FFF49345FD1DFEFBFC9DFEC7" box="[704,822,310,331]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="855">M. apicalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group are 
<taxonomicName id="4C404D59FFF49345FC6DFEFBFEB9FEEB" authority="(SAULCY)" baseAuthorityName="SAULCY" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Medon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="855" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maronitus">
<emphasis id="B934EAC8FFF49345FC6DFEFBFB96FEC7" box="[944,1085,310,331]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="855">M. maronitus</emphasis>
(SAULCY)
</taxonomicName>
(widespread from the eastern Mediterranean to Middle Asia) and 
<taxonomicName id="4C404D59FFF49345FC73FE9FFE84FE0E" authority="BERNHAUER" authorityName="BERNHAUER" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Medon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="855" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bucharicus">
<emphasis id="B934EAC8FFF49345FC73FE9FFB96FEEB" box="[942,1085,338,359]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="855">M. bucharicus</emphasis>
BERNHAUER
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry id="F357764AFFF49345FEE3FEA3FE1FFE08" box="[318,436,366,388]" name="Uzbekistan" pageId="2" pageNumber="855">Uzbekistan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F357764AFFF49345FE1FFEA3FD81FE08" box="[450,554,366,388]" name="Tajikistan" pageId="2" pageNumber="855">Tajikistan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F357764AFFF49345FDE5FEA3FD04FE0F" box="[568,687,366,387]" name="Kyrgyzstan" pageId="2" pageNumber="855">Kyrgyzstan</collectingCountry>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="EFD14B2BFFF49345FD1BFEA3FCFEFE08" author="ASSING V" box="[710,853,366,388]" pageId="2" pageNumber="855" pagination="1027 - 1034" refId="ref1245" refString="ASSING V. (2005): A revision of Western Palaearctic Medon. IV. A new species and new records from Iran, and a catalogue of species (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae, Paederinae). - Linzer biologische Beitrage 37 (2): 1027 - 1034." type="journal article" year="2005">ASSING 2005</bibRefCitation>
). From 
<taxonomicName id="4C404D59FFF49345FC77FEA3FB9CFE0F" box="[938,1079,366,387]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Medon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="855" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maronitus">
<emphasis id="B934EAC8FFF49345FC77FEA3FB9CFE0F" box="[938,1079,366,387]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="855">M. maronitus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the new species is distinguished by the broader body (especially the broader head), the coarser and less dense puncturation of the forebody, and by the shape of the aedeagus; for illustrations of the male primary and secondary sexual characters of 
<taxonomicName id="4C404D59FFF49345FC50FE0FFBBCFE5B" box="[909,1047,450,471]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Medon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="855" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maronitus">
<emphasis id="B934EAC8FFF49345FC50FE0FFBBCFE5B" box="[909,1047,450,471]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="855">M. maronitus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD14B2BFFF49345FF6FFE13FEF9FE78" author="ASSING V" box="[178,338,478,500]" pageId="2" pageNumber="855" pagination="33 - 82" refId="ref1165" refString="ASSING V. (2004 a): A revision of the Medon species of the Eastern Mediterranean and adjacent regions (Insecta: Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae). - Bonner zoologische Beitrage 52: 33 - 82." type="journal article" year="2004">ASSING (2004a</bibRefCitation>
: 
<figureCitation id="137B2A5FFFF49345FE83FE13FE13FE78" box="[350,440,478,500]" captionStart="Figs 1-7" captionStartId="1.[178,218,1237,1257]" captionTargetBox="[203,1071,308,1219]" captionTargetId="figure-51@1.[178,1093,753,1222]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs 1-7: Medon reuteri nov.sp.: (1) forebody; (2) head and pronotum; (3) elytra; (4) male sternite VII; (5) male sternite VIII; (6) aedeagus in lateral view; (7) aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 1: 1.0 mm; 2-3: 0.5 mm; 4-7: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5416628" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5416628/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="855">Figs 4-7</figureCitation>
). From 
<taxonomicName id="4C404D59FFF49345FDD3FE13FD08FE7F" box="[526,675,478,499]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Medon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="855" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bucharicus">
<emphasis id="B934EAC8FFF49345FDD3FE13FD08FE7F" box="[526,675,478,499]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="855">M. bucharicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C404D59FFF49345FD6EFE13FCB6FE7F" authorityName="Feldmann" authorityYear="2007" box="[691,797,478,499]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Medon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="855" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reuteri">
<emphasis id="B934EAC8FFF49345FD6EFE13FCB6FE7F" box="[691,797,478,499]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="855">M. reuteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is separated by its broader head, the more pronounced puncturation of the pronotum, the slightly shorter antennae, and by the shape of the aedeagus; for illustrations of 
<taxonomicName id="4C404D59FFF49345FD3DFDDBFCDFFDA7" box="[736,884,534,555]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Medon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="855" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bucharicus">
<emphasis id="B934EAC8FFF49345FD3DFDDBFCDFFDA7" box="[736,884,534,555]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="855">M. bucharicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD14B2BFFF49345FC7BFDDBFB91FDA0" author="ASSING V" box="[934,1082,534,556]" pageId="2" pageNumber="855" pagination="25 - 95" refId="ref1296" refString="ASSING V. (2006): A revision of Western Palaearctic Medon: the species of the Atlantic Islands, the Western Mediterranean, and Europe, except for the southeast (Insecta: Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae). - Bonner zoologische Beitrage 54 (2005): 25 - 95." type="journal article" year="2006">ASSING (2006</bibRefCitation>
: Figs 112-116).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFF36DAFFF49345FF6FFD9BFB83FD04" blockId="2.[178,1085,598,648]" pageId="2" pageNumber="855">
For illustrations of the male primary and secondary sexual characters of the other species of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C404D59FFF49345FF2FFDBFFECFFD0B" baseAuthorityName="Kraatz" baseAuthorityYear="1857" box="[242,356,626,647]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Medon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="855" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apicalis">
<emphasis id="B934EAC8FFF49345FF2FFDBFFECFFD0B" box="[242,356,626,647]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="855">M. apicalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group from the western Palaearctic region see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD14B2BFFF49345FC9CFDBFFC77FD04" author="ASSING V" box="[833,988,626,648]" pageId="2" pageNumber="855" pagination="33 - 82" refId="ref1165" refString="ASSING V. (2004 a): A revision of the Medon species of the Eastern Mediterranean and adjacent regions (Insecta: Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae). - Bonner zoologische Beitrage 52: 33 - 82." type="journal article" year="2004">ASSING (2004a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD14B2BFFF49345FC3BFDBFFBB6FD04" author="ASSING V" box="[998,1053,626,648]" pageId="2" pageNumber="855" pagination="25 - 95" refId="ref1296" refString="ASSING V. (2006): A revision of Western Palaearctic Medon: the species of the Atlantic Islands, the Western Mediterranean, and Europe, except for the southeast (Insecta: Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae). - Bonner zoologische Beitrage 54 (2005): 25 - 95." type="journal article" year="2006">2006</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFF36DAFFF49345FF6FFD5BFEBAFD44" blockId="2.[178,1085,662,712]" pageId="2" pageNumber="855">
E t y m o l o g y: The species is dedicated to Christoph Reuter, who collected the 
<typeStatus id="54FB8878FFF49345FF6FFD7FFEA5FD44" box="[178,270,690,712]" pageId="2" pageNumber="855">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF3F6652FFF49345FEE2F9E1FD48F9CC" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5416630" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5416630" box="[319,739,1578,1600]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5416630/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="855" startId="2.[319,352,1580,1600]" targetBox="[320,943,737,1568]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph id="8BFF36DAFFF49345FEE2F9E1FD48F9CC" blockId="2.[319,739,1578,1600]" box="[319,739,1578,1600]" pageId="2" pageNumber="855">
<emphasis id="B934EAC8FFF49345FEE2F9E1FEDEF9CC" bold="true" box="[319,373,1580,1600]" pageId="2" pageNumber="855">Fig. 8</emphasis>
: Type locality of 
<taxonomicName id="4C404D59FFF49345FDC5F9E7FD30F9CC" authority="Feldmann, 2007" authorityName="Feldmann" authorityYear="2007" box="[536,667,1578,1600]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Medon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="855" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reuteri" status="nov.sp.">
<emphasis id="B934EAC8FFF49345FDC5F9E7FD30F9CC" box="[536,667,1578,1600]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="855">Medon reuteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20757B3FFF49345FD7CF9E1FD48F9CC" box="[673,739,1580,1600]" pageId="2" pageNumber="855" rank="species">nov.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BFF36DAFFF59344FF6FFF16FE44FEC4" blockId="3.[178,1085,219,328]" pageId="3" pageNumber="856">
D i s t r i b u t i o n a n d b i o n o m i c s: The 
<typeStatus id="54FB8878FFF59344FD2EFF16FCBCFF7C" box="[755,791,219,240]" pageId="3" pageNumber="856">type</typeStatus>
locality is situated in the Chapa Dara district (
<collectingRegion id="4984F838FFF59344FE47FF35FDEEFE82" box="[410,581,248,270]" country="Afghanistan" name="Kunar" pageId="3" pageNumber="856">Kunar province</collectingRegion>
), eastern 
<collectingCountry id="F357764AFFF59344FD6EFF35FC9AFE82" box="[691,817,248,270]" name="Afghanistan" pageId="3" pageNumber="856">Afghanistan</collectingCountry>
, at an altitude of about 
<quantity id="4CB89B3FFFF59344FF6FFED8FEABFEA7" box="[178,256,277,299]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="856" unit="m" value="2000.0">2000 m</quantity>
. The species was collected in July, close to a meltwater stream in a cedar wood (
<figureCitation id="137B2A5FFFF59344FF64FEFFFF5DFEC4" box="[185,246,306,328]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[319,352,1580,1600]" captionTargetBox="[320,943,737,1568]" captionTargetId="figure-245@2.[320,943,737,1568]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 8: Type locality of Medon reuteri nov.sp." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5416630" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5416630/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="856">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
) (REUTER pers. comm.).
</paragraph>
